# Gitignored files to copy into worktrees Claude Code creates (--worktree,
# EnterWorktree, subagent worktrees, desktop sessions). Gitignore-syntax; only
# files that ALSO match .gitignore are copied (tracked files are never duped).
# Docs: https://code.claude.com/docs/en/worktrees#copy-gitignored-files-into-worktrees
#
# settings.local.json carries plugin enablement (enabledPlugins) AND the
# project permission allowlist. Without this line a fresh worktree starts with
# installed plugins OFF and prompts for permissions already granted on main.
# See skills/worktree/SKILL.md §2.
.claude/settings.local.json
# NOTE: a gitignored NESTED-REPO directory (one with its own .git) canNOT be
# carried by .worktreeinclude — this copies gitignored FILES, and git does not
# recurse into a nested-repo boundary, so the dir copies as nothing (verified
# 2026-06-20, prediction 55b1735b miss; brand-foundry never rode in). Nested
# repos like skills/brand-foundry are materialized into worktrees by
# worktree-repos.json + hooks/materialize_worktree_repos.py instead. Only single
# gitignored FILES (like settings.local.json above) belong in this file. See
# skills/nested-repos.
